\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\div(\vec{u}\phi)=\phi\div\vec{u}+\vec{u}\cdot\grad{\phi}
\]

\end_inset

which leads to
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\DDt{\phi\abs{V}}-\phi\DDt{\abs{V}}\doteq\left(\pdv{\phi}{t}+\vec{u}\cdot\grad{\phi}\right)\abs{V}\label{eq:DDtOnPhiTimesV}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

It is then natural to 
\emph on
denote
\emph default
 the parenthesized quantity in the RHS as
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\boxed{\DDt{\phi}=\pdv{\phi}{t}+\vec{u}\cdot\grad{\phi}}\label{eq:DDtAtPoint}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

which is taken as the 
\emph on
definition
\emph default
 of the 
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
derivative!material ~!~ at a point
\end_layout

\end_inset


\noun on
material derivative
\noun default
 at a point.
 The 
\begin_inset Formula $\pdv*{t}$
\end_inset

 is called the 
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
derivative!local ~
\end_layout

\end_inset


\noun on
local derivative
\noun default
 while 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{u}\cdot\grad$
\end_inset

 is called the 
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
